title: Bug 6322: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: Bug 6322: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes. JDK 1.4 includes obfuscated classes named 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', 'd', etc.
OB: The All types dialog shows the obfuscated classes prominently.
EB: The obfuscated classes should be less prominent in the All types dialog.
SR: To resolve this issue, I suggest either sorting the lower case class names after the ones that start with a capital letter or completely filtering out the obfuscated classes.
